### -----------------------
### LOCAL (when running backend locally)
### -----------------------

### Health (local root health)
GET http://localhost:3001/health

### Register dealer (local)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dealer@example.com",
  "password": "pass1234",
  "role": "dealer",
  "dealerName": "Sunrise Motors"
}

### Login (local)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dealer@example.com",
  "password": "pass1234"
}

### Create vehicle (local; uses token from login)
@access = {{login.response.body.$.access}}

POST http://localhost:3001/api/vehicles
Authorization: Bearer {{access}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vin": "1C4RJFBG0LC123456",
  "year": 2020,
  "make": "Jeep",
  "model": "Grand Cherokee",
  "trim": "Limited",
  "price": 29950,
  "mileage": 42000,
  "location": "San Rafael, CA"
}

### Search (local; note /api/search)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/search?q=jeep&pagesize=5


